This kit contains all the materials you need to make your very own 14" x 14" cross stitched Bee cushion cover:

32-count ivory evenweave cloth;
Stranded black cotton embroidery thread;
2 x needles;
Cushion backing cloth;
Pattern sheets;
Little booklet of how to.

The cushion cover is very easy to make, with no zips or buttons, but you will need your own:

Small sharp scissors;
Pins;
Sewing machine or needle & thread;
14" x 14" cushion pad;
(Optional: 21" wide roller frame or hoop in your preferred size)

The additional photographs are illustrations of the finished design - please note this listing is for the kit only.

Kits are not suitable for children.

Please <a href="http://whatdelilahdid.bigcartel.com/info">click here</a> for information on delivery costs.

You can find 14" x 14" pads <a href="http://www.thefeathercompany.com/shop/square-feather-cushions-pads/">here</a> if they are not available to you locally.

